Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo The Management of the Federal Polytechnic, Ede, Osun State, has announced the signing of a memorandum of understanding with a group, M8 Global KNOW Network, for the deployment of technological services for open distance and e-learning of the institution. A statement by Sola Lawal, the Public Relations Officer of the polytechnic, on Monday, said approval for the programme had initially been granted by the National Board for Technical Education for the implementation of the National E-learning Strategic Plan for Technical and Vocational Education and Training. The Rector of the institution, Dr John Adekolawole, while speaking at the ceremony where the MoU was signed, lauded the initiative, adding that the agreement would go a long way in making the distance learning programme of the poly more functional. Copyright PUNCH.
